            "name": "Riddler's Rune",
            "saving_throw": [
              {
                "dc": 26,
                "save_type": "Will",
                "subtype": "save_dc",
                "text": "DC 26 Will save",
                "type": "stat_block_section"
              }
            ],
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "Once per week, Neshkefru can create a magical symbol as the rune trap ritual. She usually shapes it to take the form of a written riddle and sets the password to the answer. A creature that gives the wrong answer or tries to pass without answering must succeed at a DC 26 Will save or be affected by one of the following spells, chosen by the sphinx when creating the symbol: *synaptic pulse* (5th), *charm* (4th), *fear* (4th), *phantom pain* (4th), *sleep* (4th). The sphinx learns the identity of any creature that answers the riddle and tends to be friendly to them if they answered correctly.",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "name": "Riddler's Rune",
          "offensive_action_type": "ability",
          "subtype": "offensive_action",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
